com.b2international.commons.dynamic

Class AbstractDynamicValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.b2international.commons.dynamic.AbstractDynamicValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DynamicValue
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractDynamicMap, DynamicValueImpl

    public abstract class AbstractDynamicValue
extends Object
implements DynamicValue
    Abstract implementation of DynamicValue that handles as(Class) and as(Class, Object) methods and offers reasonable defaults for the rest of the interface.

      • asBoolean

        public boolean asBoolean(boolean defaultValue)
        Returns the encapsulated object as a boolean primitive if it is an instance of Boolean, defaultValue otherwise. This method is the equivalent of calling as(Boolean.class, defaultValue).booleanValue().

        This implementation always returns defaultValue; subclasses should override.

        Specified by:
        asBoolean in interface DynamicValue
        Parameters:
